# Frontend Architecture

> Frontend only. See also: `core.mdc` · `api.mdc`

**Stack:** Next.js (App Router) + [Feature-Sliced Design (FSD)](https://fsd.how/).

## Next.js and FSD Integration

Next.js and FSD conflict over the `app` and `pages` folders. The fix follows the [official FSD guide for Next.js](https://fsd.how/docs/guides/tech/with-nextjs/#app-router).

### Project Structure

```
app/                        # Next.js App Router — thin routing layer
├── layout.tsx              # Page Layout
└── [route]/page.tsx        # re-export pages from the FSD pages layer

pages/
└── README.md               # stub to avoid Next.js Pages Router conflict

src/                        # all FSD layers
├── app/                    # FSD App layer (providers, api, styles)
├── pages/                  # FSD Pages layer
│   └── [page-name]/
├── widgets/
├── features/
├── entities/
└── shared/
```

### Integration Rules

1. **Next.js `app`** (root `app/`) — routing only. Re-exports pages from the FSD `src/pages/` layer.
2. **Root `pages/`** — contains only `README.md` as a stub. Prevents Next.js from treating `src/pages/` as the Pages Router. Required even when empty.
3. **FSD layers** (all under `src/`) — business logic and UI. The FSD `app` layer (`src/app/`) is separate from the Next.js `app/` folder.

### Page Re-export Example

```tsx
// app/example/page.tsx
export { ExamplePage } from '@/pages/example';
```

## FSD Layers

Layers are ordered top to bottom by decreasing responsibility. Each layer contains **slices** (by business domain); each slice contains **segments** (`ui`, `api`, `model`, `lib`, `config`).

| Layer        | Purpose                                          | Examples                              |
| ------------ | ------------------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------- |
| **app**      | App initialization, providers, global styles     | `providers`, `styles`                 |
| **pages**    | Full pages — composition of widgets and features | `home`, `todo-list`                   |
| **widgets**  | Large self-contained UI blocks                   | `header`, `todo-list-panel`           |
| **features** | User scenarios and actions                       | `create-todo`, `toggle-todo`          |
| **entities** | Business entities                                | `todo`, `user`                        |
| **shared**   | Reusable code with no domain coupling            | `ui`, `lib`, `api`, `config`, `model` |

### Segments Within a Slice

| Segment  | Purpose                             |
| -------- | ----------------------------------- |
| `ui`     | React components                    |
| `api`    | Requests, data/query hooks, actions |
| `model`  | Types, stores, business logic       |
| `lib`    | Slice-specific helper functions     |
| `config` | Slice configuration                 |

Server code is not a standalone segment — it lives inside the relevant segment under a `server/` subfolder (see "Server Code" below).

## Import Direction

Imports are allowed **top-down only** — from upper layers into lower layers.

```
app → pages → widgets → features → entities → shared
```

### Allowed

- `features/create-todo` imports from `entities/todo`, `shared/ui`
- `pages/home` imports from `widgets/header`, `features/create-todo`

### Forbidden

- Importing from an upper layer into a lower one (`shared` → `features`)
- Cross-imports between slices on the same layer (`features/create-todo` → `features/delete-todo`)

For public API and import rules, see `core.mdc` — **Import Through Slice Public API Only**.

## Server Code

Server components, functions, and variables live inside a `server/` subfolder **within the corresponding segment** — not at the slice root. Each `server/` folder exports through its own `index.ts`.

Importing from `api/server/` is an exception to the slice public API rule — see `core.mdc` — **Deep Imports — Exceptions Only**. For naming and usage, see `api.mdc`.

```ts
// ✅ Server import through segment server public API
import { createTodoAction } from '@/features/create-todo/api/server';
import { queryClient } from '@/shared/api/server';

// ❌ Server code through the client API
import { createTodoAction } from '@/features/create-todo';
```

## Navigation

All navigation paths live in `src/shared/model/navigation` as the `navigationMap` constant.

```ts
// src/shared/model/navigation.ts
export const navigationMap = {
  home: '/',
  todos: '/todos',
  todoDetail: (id: string) => `/todos/${id}`,
} as const;
```

```tsx
import { navigationMap } from '@/shared/model';
import Link from 'next/link';

<Link href={navigationMap.todos}>Todos</Link>;
```

Hardcoded paths (`'/todos'`) in components are forbidden.

## Import Aliases

Always use aliases instead of relative paths between layers. See `core/code-style.mdc`. Base alias: `@/` → `src/`.

## Internationalization

All user-facing text goes through [next-intl](https://next-intl.dev/). Hardcoded strings in components are forbidden.

```tsx
const t = useTranslations('CreateTodo');
return <button>{t('submit')}</button>;
```

Translations live in `src/shared/lib/i18n/`.
